pageContext.claim: “We built a brand new wall [in San Diego]. That’s not a renovated wall, that’s a brand new wall. We took down the old wall, we built a brand new wall. It’s fantastic, looks great, they did a great job, totally stopped everybody from coming in.”
pageContext.analysis: The renovated fencing that was built in San Diego "isn't Trump's wall," a spokesman for the Border Patrol told the Los Angeles Times. Plus the construction plans began in 2009 under the Obama administration and were funded in 2017 under Trump.
